data.name: dm
data.description: Type of disambiguation applied. It is accumulative, that is, the semantic disambiguation mode will also include morphosyntactic disambiguation

data.name: lang
data.description: It specifies the language in which the text must be analyzed.

data.name: rt
data.description: Deal with relaxed typography. This parameter indicates how reliable the text (as far as spelling, typography, etc. are concerned) to analyze is, and influences how strict the engine will be when it comes to take these factors into account in the topic extraction.

data.name: sdg
data.description: Semantic disambiguation grouping. This parameter will only apply when semantic disambiguation is activated (dm=s).

data.name: timeref
data.description: This value allows to set a specific time reference to detect the actual value of all the relative time expressions detected in the text. Format: YYYY-MM-DD hh:mm:ss GMT±HH:MM

data.name: tt
data.description: The list of topic types to extract will be specified through a string with the letters assigned to each one of the topic types that are to be extracted.

data.name: txt
data.description: Input text that's going to be analyzed.
data.value: Robert Downey Jr has topped Forbes magazine's annual list of the highest paid actors for the second year in a row. The 49-year-old star of the Iron Man and Avengers films made an estimated $75m over the past year, beating rivals Dwayne Johnson, Bradley Cooper, Chris Hemsworth and Leonardo DiCaprio.

data.name: txtf
data.description: The text format parameter specifies if the text included in the txt parameter uses markup language that needs to be interpreted (known HTML tags and HTML code will be interpreted, and unknown tags will be ignored).

data.name: ud
data.description: The user dictionary allows to include user-defined entities and concepts in the topics extraction.

data.name: uw
data.description: Deal with unknown words. This feature adds a stage to the topic extraction in which the engine, much like a spellchecker, tries to find a suitable analysis to the unknown words resulted from the initial analysis assignment. It is specially useful to decrease the impact typos have in text analyses.

Topics Extraction 2.0 is MeaningCloud's solution for extracting the different elements present in sources of information. This detection process is carried out by combining a number of complex natural language processing techniques that allow to obtain morphological, syntactic and semantic analyses of a text and use them to identify different types of significant elements.
